subSection.paragraph:
The fern 

Drynaria roosii
Nakaike

(
Polypodiaceae
) is widely distributed in South 
China
. Its rhizomes are used as the traditional Chinese medicine Gu-Sui-Bu for treatment of osteoporosis and bone fractures (
Liang et al., 2011a
). Previous studies indicated that the main components in 

D. roosii

are flavonoids, phenylpropanoids, lignans and triterpenes (
Chang et al., 2003
; 
Liang et al., 2010a
, 
2010b
, 
2011a
, 
2011b
; 
Wang et al., 2008a
, 
2008b
, 2010). Among them, phenylpropanoids and lignans exhibited various biological activities, including anti-inflammatory (
Cheng et al., 2017
; 
Zhang et al., 2018
; 
Zheng et al., 2014
), cytotoxic (
Rangkaew et al., 2009
; 
Ye et al., 2021
) and antioxidant (
Chang et al., 2010
; 
Gao et al., 2017
) activities, etc. Therefore, we conducted a study on the chemical constituents of 

D. roosii

to search for more bioactive phenylpropanoids and lignans. Herein, we describe the isolation, structure elucidation and cytotoxic activity of five undescribed bis(lauric acid-12-yl)lignanoates that we named as liglaurates A–E (
1–5
) (
Fig. 1
), together with the known methyl 12-caffeoyloxylaurate (
6
) (
Sui et al., 2015
) and glyceryl 12-caffeoyloxylaurate (
7
) (
Liang et al., 2010a
).

Two known compounds, methyl 12-caffeoyloxylaurate (
6
) (
Sui et al., 2015
) and glyceryl 12-caffeoyloxylaurate (
7
) (
Liang et al., 2010a
) were identified by comparison of their NMR data (
Table S1
) with those reported in the literature.

Theoretical calculations of ECD spectra for compounds 
1–4
were performed with Gaussian 09 (
Frisch et al., 2010
; 
Zhang et al., 2018
). The preliminary conformational distributions search was carried out by SYBYL-X 2.0 software. The ground-state geometries were optimized at the B3LYP/6-31G(d) level. The ECD of the selected conformers with distributions higher than 1% were then calculated by the TD-DFT method at the B3LYP/6-31G(d) level with the PCM model in methanol solution. The calculated ECD spectra were produced by SpecDis 1.70.1 (
Bruhn et al., 2017
).

The DPPH radical-scavenging assay was carried out as described previously (
Xu et al., 2021
).

The ORAC assay was carried out as described previously (
Xu et al., 2021
).
